21 // If the coefficient is greater that 2^63 - 1, express it as a pair [a, b]
22 // which is combined with a*2^52 + b. The largest coefficient is
23 // 831281402884796906843926125 = 0x2af9eaf25d149c52a73ee6d =
24 // 0x2af9eaf25d * 2^52 + 0x149c52a73ee6d which is less than 2^90.
25 // Both a and b are less that 2^52 and so are exactly representable by
26 // doubles; then the computation of the full double coefficient involves only
27 // a single rounding operation.
28

7863 GEOGRAPHICLIB_STATIC_ASSERT(sizeof(coeff) / sizeof(real) ==
7864 (nC4_ * (nC4_ + 1) * (nC4_ + 5)) / 6,
7865 "Coefficient array size mismatch in C4coeff");
7866 int o = 0, k = 0;
7867 for (int l = 0; l < nC4_; ++l) { // l is index of C4[l]
7868 for (int j = nC4_ - 1; j >= l; --j) { // coeff of eps^j
7869 int m = nC4_ - j - 1; // order of polynomial in n
7870 _C4x[k++] = Math::polyval(m, coeff + o, _n) / coeff[o + m + 1];
7871 o += m + 2;
7872 }
7873 }
7874 // Post condition: o == sizeof(coeff) / sizeof(real) && k == nC4x_
7875 if (!(o == sizeof(coeff) / sizeof(real) && k == nC4x_))
7876 throw GeographicErr("C4 misalignment");
7877 }
